        "blog.posts.como-escribir-guiones-virales-tiktok-2025.category": "TikTok",
        "blog.posts.como-escribir-guiones-virales-tiktok-2025.content": "<h2>Why Scripts Are Key to TikTok Success</h2>\n\n<p>In 2025, TikTok has over 1.5 billion active users. Competition is fierce, but with a good script, you can stand out. Here's how.</p>\n\n<h3>The 3 Elements of a Viral Script</h3>\n\n<p><strong>1. Irresistible hook (first 3 seconds)</strong></p>\n<p>You have 3 seconds to capture attention. Use provocative questions, surprising statements, or clear promises.</p>\n\n<p>Effective hook examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"This trick got me 100K followers in 2 weeks...\"</li>\n<li>\"Did you know 99% of people are doing this WRONG?\"</li>\n<li>\"I'm going to show you something your competition doesn't want you to know\"</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>2. Clear and concise development</strong></p>\n<p>Keep each sentence short. Use conversational language. Eliminate unnecessary words.</p>\n\n<p><strong>3. Call-to-action (CTA) at the end</strong></p>\n<p>Don't forget to ask for engagement: \"Follow for more\", \"Comment your opinion\", \"Save this video\".</p>\n\n<h3>Script structure that works</h3>\n\n<pre>\nSeconds 0-3: Impactful hook\nSeconds 4-10: Problem presentation\nSeconds 11-40: Step-by-step solution\nSeconds 41-60: Summary and CTA\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Pro tips</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Write as you speak:</strong> TikTok is conversational, not formal</li>\n<li><strong>Use transitions:</strong> \"But wait...\", \"And here's the best part...\", \"Now watch this...\"</li>\n<li><strong>Create loops:</strong> Reference the beginning at the end so they watch again</li>\n<li><strong>Optimize for audio:</strong> Read your script out loud before recording</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Free tools to write scripts</h3>\n\n<p>You don't need to be a professional writer. Use our <a href='/tiktok/script-writer'>AI script generation tool</a> to create viral scripts in seconds.</p>\n\n<h3>Common mistakes to avoid</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>‚ùå Starting with \"Hi, my name is...\"</li>\n<li>‚ùå Scripts too long (more than 90 seconds)</li>\n<li>‚ùå Not including subtitles in the script</li>\n<li>‚ùå Forgetting the CTA at the end</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n\n<p>A good script is the difference between 100 and 100,000 views. Start with a strong hook, keep valuable content, and end with a clear CTA. And remember: practice makes perfect.</p>",

